modules.description: This module provides functions to convert between a structured representation of values and a MessagePack format. It supports operations to view a MessagePack value as a structured type and to build a MessagePack value from a structured view. It works directly with `Msgpck.t` and structured representations using `Json_repr.view`. Useful for serializing and deserializing complex data structures to and from MessagePack while maintaining a consistent intermediate format.

This module converts values between JSON and MessagePack formats using JSON encodings, enabling efficient serialization and deserialization of structured data. It supports constructing MessagePack values from JSON-encoded inputs and reconstructing structured views from MessagePack using `Msgpck.t` and `Json_repr.view`. The child module extends this by allowing direct manipulation of MessagePack values as structured types, facilitating operations like viewing or building MessagePack data with precise control. Examples include converting JSON-encoded data structures into compact MessagePack for transmission, or reconstructing structured values from MessagePack binaries for processing.
